1
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:10,940
♪Hush now, don't disturb
the moonlight on the pond♪

2
00:00:11,940 --> 00:00:14,900
♪A shattered heart
rests pillowed in my chest♪

3
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:17,580
♪I would shield you♪

4
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:20,580
♪From this cruel wind and frost♪

5
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:25,460
♪The russet cloth
brushes against my heart♪

6
00:00:26,420 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Like sunset
draping over your shoulders♪

7
00:00:30,020 --> 00:00:31,580
♪This lingering afterglow♪

8
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:35,420
♪Holds the image
of our very first glance♪

9
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:40,100
♪I borrow a thousand-year wind
to caress your gauze window♪

10
00:00:40,460 --> 00:00:44,420
♪Tailoring moonlight
into your luminous gown♪

11
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:50,820
♪Severing the past,
weaving a thousand yards of splendor♪

12
00:00:51,380 --> 00:00:54,980
♪With a thousand-year dream,
I seek the fragrance of your hair♪

13
00:00:55,220 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Pouring a lifetime of passion
into the silk you wear♪

14
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:05,660
♪In this splendid world,
wherever you are is paradise♪

15
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:12,460
=The Silk Master from the Future=

16
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:17,460
=Episode 6=
(This story is entirely fictional.)

17
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:18,520
Prefect,

18
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:20,960
may I request a brief pause
before the counsel?

19
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:23,320
What is it? Speak.

20
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,120
So you're Li Yunhe,
the Zhou live-in son-in-law, right?

21
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:29,480
That's me.

22
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,680
(Daqian's Poet Laureate)
I heard you posed a verse the other day.

23
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:34,520
The first line being
"Smoke veils the pond-side willow."

24
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,600
Is that true?

25
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:37,000
Ah, I see.

26
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:39,920
So you're here to help your master

27
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:41,800
look good with a verse match, huh?

28
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,920
Well, well,

29
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,840
Li Yunhe,

30
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,680
stop playing the big shot.

31
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:47,920
You think you're worthy

32
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:50,280
of Mr. Lu bothering to
make a move against you?

33
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,480
Well, well,

34
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,800
you again.

35
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,400
In a verse match,

36
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:55,880
winning and losing is normal.

37
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,480
Admitting you were outmatched

38
00:01:58,720 --> 00:01:59,880
is nothing to be ashamed of.

39
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:02,480
Li Yunhe.

40
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:03,880
I admit your first line

41
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:05,920
does have some depth.

42
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,160
But as for the matching line,

43
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,200
I bet even you can't come up with one.

44
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,920
If you can't handle it, don't compete.

45
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:12,280
I can't be bothered

46
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,200
to argue with you.

47
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:19,280
See this?

48
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:22,080
This is a 1,000-tael silver note.

49
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:27,120
If you can match that line,

50
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,440
this thousand taels will be...

51
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:31,200
My lord, you truly are generous.

52
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,360
You're like the God of Wealth.

53
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:34,880
I'll accept it without further ado.

54
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,160
You'd better think this through.

55
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:41,120
This thousand taels of silver

56
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,000
is not so easy to earn.

57
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,400
Don't worry, my lord,
you'll be satisfied.

58
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:48,080
What is going on?

59
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,520
Why does this guy
keep popping up everywhere?

60
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:51,760
He's just a broke, illiterate nobody.

61
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,640
It's one thing for him to peddle goods,

62
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:55,640
but now he even dares to tear down

63
00:02:55,640 --> 00:02:56,400
official government proclamations?

64
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,120
A broke, illiterate nobody?

65
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:00,240
Who are you calling
a broke, illiterate nobody?

66
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,360
That's the Zhou family's son-in-law!

67
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:01,800
He managed...

68
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,240
Chunxiang.

69
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:04,160
Don't argue with others.

70
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:05,960
My lady,

71
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,880
she called Mr. Li a nobody.

72
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:10,000
(He comes from a ruined family)

73
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,160
(and is illiterate...)

74
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:13,040
(That's what the outside world
says about you.)

75
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,760
(But why is it that the real you)

76
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:16,200
(is brimming with talent,)

77
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,200
(well-read and ambitious?)

78
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,360
(Li Yunhe,)

79
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,760
(just how many secrets are you hiding?)

80
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:23,640
Li Yunhe,

81
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:25,240
I'll bear witness here.

82
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,800
If you can come up with

83
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,200
the second line
to "Smoke veils the pond-side willow,"

84
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:32,880
this thousand-tael silver note
will be yours.

85
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,680
But if you fail...

86
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:37,240
I'll return

87
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:38,520
a thousand taels in full

88
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,440
and accept your judgment, Prefect.

89
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,040
Alright.

90
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:49,120
Smoke veils the pond-side willow.

91
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:50,800
It conceals the five elements within it

92
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,200
and carries profound poetic imagery.

93
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,440
This first line truly has substance.

94
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:56,400
Guess what?

95
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,600
The Zhou's son-in-law composed that.

96
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,800
That line was composed by Li Yunhe?

97
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:01,640
Of course.

98
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,560
It's not surprising a live-in son-in-law

99
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,360
from a merchant family can sell things,

100
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:09,440
but to think he can compose verses, too.

101
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,760
It seems our Daqian Dynasty

102
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:13,400
truly has hidden geniuses

103
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,240
and talents emerging
in every generation.

104
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:16,600
Perhaps

105
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:19,160
he just heard that line
from somewhere else.

106
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,760
(Li Yunhe, you can do it.)

107
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,760
(I believe in you.)

108
00:04:22,840 --> 00:04:24,080
(You composed the first line yourself.)

109
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,600
(You can definitely match it.)

110
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:31,800
Li Yunhe,

111
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,120
(Daqian's Poet Laureate)
are you done pacing yet?

112
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:36,840
Exactly.

113
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,960
(Daqian's Poet Laureate)
If you can't match it,

114
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:40,240
(Daqian's Poet Laureate)
return the silver note

115
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:42,320
and accept your punishment
on your knees.

116
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:44,600
What's the use of putting on an act?

117
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:46,720
Listen closely.

118
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,600
My first line is:

119
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,720
Smoke veils the pond-side willow.

120
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,760
My matching line is:

121
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,400
(Daqian's Poet Laureate)

122
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:03,040
Cannons guard the sea-fort tower.

123
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,480
- Bravo!
- Incredible!

124
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,800
Truly brilliant.

125
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,040
Smoke veils the pond-side willow.

126
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,280
Cannons guard the sea-fort tower.

127
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:16,560
He actually matched it.

128
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:18,080
Mr. Li matched it!

129
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,960
My lady, I told you he could do it!

130
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:22,360
That second line must be copied, too.

131
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:25,400
Well?

132
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,520
I don't know where

133
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:29,720
(Daqian's Poet Laureate)
you copied that from,

134
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,320
but

135
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,600
(Daqian's Poet Laureate)
since you've matched the verse,

136
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:35,680
(Daqian's Poet Laureate)
guess you do have a bit of talent.

137
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,560
Isn't that right, Prefect?

138
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:38,840
You're right,

139
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:39,880
my lord.

140
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:41,640
Li Yunhe,

141
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,480
you've preliminarily passed my test.

142
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:46,600
But matching verses

143
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,560
is a mere parlor trick.

144
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:49,640
A true

145
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:51,000
pillar of the state

146
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:53,360
must be able to manage the household

147
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:55,240
and serve in the court.

148
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:56,680
Guards,

149
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:59,680
return the official proclamation
that Mr. Li tore down

150
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:01,000
to him.

151
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,300
(Proclamation)

152
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:08,360
Chunxiang, go find out

153
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:09,600
what that proclamation in his hand

154
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,520
is about right away.

155
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,520
The proclamation
posted by the Feng City Prefect

156
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,800
is the only one recently.

157
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,520
The areas around Feng City are flooded,

158
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,120
refugees are flooding in,

159
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,400
and grain prices are soaring,
affecting livelihoods.

160
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,680
The Prefect posted the proclamation

161
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,680
to seek strategies
for governance and relief.

162
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,920
Strategies for governance?

163
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:29,200
But Mr. Li
doesn't understand these things.

164
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,480
Why would he tear it down?

165
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,080
If I'm not mistaken,

166
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:35,040
this must be a scheme
by Lu Qifeng and his people

167
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,480
targeting Li Yunhe.

168
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:40,200
What...

169
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,160
What about my...

170
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,520
(Now I get it.)

171
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,240
(They used 1,000 taels)

172
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,880
(and a verse match
to set a trap for me.)

173
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:48,920
(Once I took the money,)

174
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,160
(the official proclamation would)

175
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,560
(be slapped right in my face.)

176
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,240
(If I couldn't match the verse,)

177
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,360
(they would use)

178
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,760
(their earlier words to corner me.)

179
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,600
(What a clever chain of schemes.)

180
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,600
Since you've already torn down
the government proclamation

181
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:07,040
and the 1,000-tael reward

182
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,000
is already in your pocket,

183
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,280
regarding the governance strategy,

184
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:13,080
do you have a sound plan?

185
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,560
Li Yunhe,

186
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:20,280
you've already pocketed
the silver note from that proclamation.

187
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:21,840
Now,

188
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:26,760
I hope you won't disappoint me.

189
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:27,800
What...

190
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,760
What if the plan I propose

191
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:31,760
fails?

192
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,560
Then you'll be imprisoned
for three months,

193
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,440
charged with contempt of the government,

194
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:37,520
and to be executed.

195
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:38,680
My lord.

196
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:39,920
My lord,

197
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:44,400
this offense can only warrant
a month in jail at most

198
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:48,920
and then three months of penal labor.

199
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:52,680
Alright then.

200
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,480
Three months is still a lot.

201
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,240
(Play games with me?)

202
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,680
(You won't live to finish the game.)

203
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:06,000
Yunzhuo, is this even by the book?

204
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,640
Strictly speaking,
no, it's not by the book.

205
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:10,560
But as long as the Prefect insists

206
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,600
that the money is the reward
from the proclamation,

207
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,200
and if Li Yunhe fails to provide a plan,

208
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,640
he can indeed be convicted.

209
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,200
May I ask,

210
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,040
if he truly can't answer,

211
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,600
is there any other way to get him out?

212
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,200
Afterwards,

213
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,920
he can pay a fine to the Prefect

214
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,200
to avoid the hardship of penal labor.

215
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,120
But the exact amount

216
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:33,200
depends on what the Prefect says.

217
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:35,200
Chunxiang, go back and fetch money now.

218
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,280
Bring as much as you can.

219
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:37,480
Prepare to bail him out.

220
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:41,400
(Li Yunhe, don't worry.)

221
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,760
(The Marquis House
is targeting you because of me.)

222
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,440
(I'll definitely see you safely
through this.)

223
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:51,360
The contents
of the government proclamation,

224
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,600
you've read them clearly, right?

225
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:56,840
So, do you have a strategy
to address it?

226
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:58,200
Yes.

227
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:58,720
Hmm?

228
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,400
What arrogant boasting.

229
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,960
If you claimed to be skilled in art,

230
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:03,920
that would be one thing.

231
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,880
But statecraft?

232
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,360
How could you possibly comprehend it?

233
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:08,760
You'd better think this through.

234
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,840
This concerns the people's livelihood.

235
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:13,720
If you admit defeat now,

236
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,720
at most, you'll get
three months of penal labor.

237
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:18,040
But if you continue to ignore the risk

238
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,800
and spout nonsense,

239
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:20,920
then...

240
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,200
It's precisely because this matter

241
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,520
involves the realm, the state,

242
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:25,840
and the people's welfare,

243
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,480
that I cannot

244
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:28,960
in good conscience decline.

245
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:34,760
Then tell us your proposed plan.

246
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:36,440
Prefect,

247
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,240
we're right
at the Dragon Boat Festival season.

248
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:43,040
As the saying goes, the waters of
the dragon boats come from the heavens,

249
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,840
rushing to the sea, never to return.

250
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,440
Why not take advantage
of the easing rainy season

251
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:50,040
to hold a grand dragon boat regatta?

252
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,280
A dragon boat regatta?

253
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,000
Well,

254
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:56,280
Feng City does have
such a folk tradition,

255
00:09:57,160 --> 00:10:00,600
but it's usually
just contests between villages.

256
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,520
Why not expand its influence

257
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,240
and add the prize money?

258
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:10,120
I happen to have
1,000 taels of silver here,

259
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,320
which I won from...

260
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,840
What was his name again?

261
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,120
Are you serious?

262
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:16,440
This is Lu Qifeng,
heir to the Marquis of Zhennan.

263
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:16,880
Right.

264
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:19,400
Lu Qifeng,
heir to the Marquis of Zhennan.

265
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,200
I won this from him in a verse match

266
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,480
as the prize.

267
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:24,800
I'm willing to donate
this entire 1,000 taels.

268
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:28,520
Mr. Lu Qifeng,

269
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:32,880
how much are you planning to donate?

270
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,000
My lord,

271
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:35,840
well...

272
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,040
I'll donate 1,000 taels then.

273
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,360
Good!

274
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:42,360
You're truly generous, my lord.

275
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,200
Well?

276
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,600
Your master just donated 1,000 taels.

277
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,520
Aren't you going to show some goodwill?

278
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,240
Huh?

279
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:49,280
Huh?

280
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:50,480
Li Yunhe,

281
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,520
we're discussing
disaster relief right now.

282
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,400
Don't change the subject.

283
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:57,040
(Mr. Chen wouldn't
happen to be broke, would he?)

284
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,680
This gentleman's words miss the mark.

285
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,080
I think

286
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,120
Li Yunhe has already

287
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:07,400
grasped the crux of the matter.

288
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,280
Holding a dragon boat race

289
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:10,720
can honor the Dragon King,

290
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,040
pray for favorable weather,

291
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:14,000
and seek good fortune.

292
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,960
It will mobilize Feng City's
officials and wealthy merchants

293
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,720
to come to sponsor and participate.

294
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,000
Sir,

295
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:20,880
you do get me.

296
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,760
Hold a dragon boat race

297
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:26,320
and attract officials
and wealthy merchants to participate?

298
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:27,680
In the blink of an eye,

299
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:28,880
we can accumulate

300
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:30,640
a sizable portion of relief funds.

301
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,240
Not bad.

302
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,280
I like it.

303
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:36,080
Thank you for your praise, Prefect.

304
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:37,880
Sir,

305
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:39,640
this concerns disaster relief.

306
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,000
It affects people's livelihood.

307
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:43,400
You're the Marquis's heir's lapdog.

308
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:44,760
Surely you wouldn't

309
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:47,400
forsake righteousness for petty gain,
would you?

310
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,440
I have no problem donating.

311
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,640
But according to your proposal,

312
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:53,400
just racing a few dragon boats?

313
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,320
What great result can that achieve?

314
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:57,680
The dragon boat race
is only the first step.

315
00:11:58,120 --> 00:12:00,240
During the event, we widely post notices

316
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,840
to attract merchants
from surrounding areas

317
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,640
to come and sell their goods.

318
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,800
During the races,

319
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,840
we'll open up
prime advertising and sponsorship slots

320
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,120
for major businesses.

321
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:10,640
People from nearby regions,

322
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:12,680
drawn by the fame,
will travel to Feng City,

323
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,040
spending money and consuming goods.

324
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:15,840
Wouldn't that be a natural outcome?

325
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,240
Well said. What a good idea!

326
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:21,000
This move could indeed serve
as a measure

327
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,400
to revitalize Feng City.

328
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,920
Once the dragon boat race begins,

329
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:26,800
merchants will gather,

330
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:29,280
and money
will naturally start flowing in.

331
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:30,360
Secondly,

332
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,640
the recent heavy rains

333
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:33,280
have flooded countless fertile fields.

334
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:36,000
With the funds
raised from the dragon boat event,

335
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,800
we can build water conservancy projects

336
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:38,720
and provide work relief.

337
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,920
Indirectly, this will also
mobilize the disaster victims.

338
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:42,520
Work relief?

339
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:43,880
Work relief

340
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:45,120
with a proper cause.

341
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,880
The victims can not only be resettled,

342
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:49,000
but the funds
for the early stages of the race

343
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,200
can also start flowing.

344
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:50,880
Brilliant.

345
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:51,920
Truly brilliant!

346
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,720
This is utter nonsense.

347
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,360
Feng City has been a land
of fish and rice since ancient times.

348
00:12:58,040 --> 00:12:59,920
There are starving people now

349
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,400
because we have grain shortages

350
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,360
and rising prices.

351
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:03,920
Your proposals

352
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:05,920
won't help at all.

353
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:06,960
Exactly.

354
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:08,560
Feng City

355
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:10,520
has been wealthy since ancient times,

356
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:11,560
with abundant grain harvests.

357
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,600
Now there is no grain.

358
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:15,440
What exactly are you trying to do?

359
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,800
My lord, you're absolutely right.

360
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,800
Although

361
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:22,440
the government granaries
still have some reserves,

362
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:24,800
we cannot open them recklessly.

363
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:28,040
The common people are short of grain.

364
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:30,160
Although the government
has already purchased grain

365
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:31,440
and set up porridge stations for relief,

366
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:34,000
the refugees
just keep flooding in endlessly.

367
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:36,840
It's a mere drop in the bucket.

368
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:39,400
On top of that,
grain prices are skyrocketing.

369
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:40,560
Alas.

370
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:44,240
(What's taking Chunxiang)

371
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:45,640
(so long with the money?)

372
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,320
(Li Yunhe, if you can answer,
then answer.)

373
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,400
(If not, wait for me to bail you out.)

374
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:52,040
(Whatever you do,
don't do anything reckless.)

375
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:59,760
Li Yunhe, if you can't do it,
just give up.

376
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:03,880
Prefect, may I ask,

377
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:05,760
what's the current market price
of grain?

378
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:09,280
100 coins per hodful.

379
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:11,200
And what was the price
before the disaster?

380
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,640
10 coins per hodful.

381
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,720
That means a tenfold increase.

382
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:16,440
Correct.

383
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:18,880
No wonder the people can't afford grain.

384
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:20,320
Li Yunhe,

385
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:22,760
cut the useless chatter.

386
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:24,080
Grain prices are up,

387
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:24,920
and the people have no grain.

388
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:26,280
Even a three-year-old knows that.

389
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:28,360
What we want is your solution!

390
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:30,200
Prefect,

391
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:32,000
I suspect Li Yunhe

392
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:32,880
has no plan at all.

393
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:33,880
Right now,

394
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:35,880
he's merely stalling for time.

395
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:37,560
Li Yunhe,

396
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,480
stop beating around the bush.

397
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,840
Answer me,

398
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,400
do you have a plan or not?

399
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:46,120
What's so difficult about that?

400
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:47,920
Prefect, please issue

401
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:49,600
an official proclamation,

402
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:52,960
stating that the current
market price of grain

403
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,360
is 180 coins per hodful.

404
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,280
Raise grain prices?

405
00:14:58,120 --> 00:14:59,880
I knew
you were harboring sinister intentions.

406
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:01,920
With refugees everywhere,

407
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:03,680
instead of ordering merchants
to lower prices,

408
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:05,720
you're leading the government
to drive up grain prices?

409
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:06,520
Are you

410
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:08,160
trying to incite a rebellion?

411
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:09,480
You're plunging the people

412
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:11,280
into deeper misery!

413
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,480
If the people's grievances
fester too deeply,

414
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,720
won't it lead to catastrophe?

415
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,520
Prefect, he is deceiving the public
with wicked words.

416
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,440
He should be arrested and punished!

417
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:20,400
You're right.

418
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,200
Li Yunhe,

419
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,600
is this your plan?

420
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:24,320
Guards!

421
00:15:53,020 --> 00:15:56,620
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

422
00:15:56,780 --> 00:15:59,980
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

423
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:03,220
♪Who took the March rain♪

424
00:16:03,460 --> 00:16:06,820
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

425
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:09,980
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

426
00:16:10,140 --> 00:16:13,340
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

427
00:16:14,220 --> 00:16:20,140
♪Needle and thread
stitch away the marks of time♪

428
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:23,620
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

429
00:16:23,860 --> 00:16:26,700
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

430
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:29,140
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

431
00:16:29,140 --> 00:16:33,340
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

432
00:16:33,420 --> 00:16:36,700
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

433
00:16:36,860 --> 00:16:39,980
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

434
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:43,420
♪In this life I'd be a cloud-tailor♪

435
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:50,100
♪Never failing the stars,
nor failing you♪

436
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:19,900
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

437
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:23,300
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

438
00:17:23,900 --> 00:17:26,620
♪Who took the March rain♪

439
00:17:26,820 --> 00:17:30,140
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

440
00:17:30,540 --> 00:17:33,420
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

441
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:37,220
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

442
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:40,540
♪Warp and weft entwine,
one shuttle, one dream♪

443
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:43,500
♪As seasons change♪

444
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:47,140
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

445
00:17:47,140 --> 00:17:49,980
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

446
00:17:50,060 --> 00:17:52,620
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

447
00:17:52,620 --> 00:17:56,700
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

448
00:17:56,700 --> 00:18:00,020
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

449
00:18:00,020 --> 00:18:03,740
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

450
00:18:04,140 --> 00:18:07,260
♪Washing away
a lifetime of wear and tear♪

451
00:18:07,260 --> 00:18:10,140
♪Only for you♪

452
00:18:10,140 --> 00:18:13,740
♪On the street of golden honors,
the music rises♪

453
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:16,620
♪The moon moves west
beyond the pavilion♪

454
00:18:16,740 --> 00:18:19,300
♪Wine runs dry, yet the revelry lingers♪

455
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:23,380
♪In silk, I seek a kindred soul♪

456
00:18:23,380 --> 00:18:26,700
♪The rain has ceased,
clouds begin to clear♪

457
00:18:26,740 --> 00:18:30,100
♪The fragrant silk billows
under the low-hung stars♪

458
00:18:30,940 --> 00:18:36,620
♪I'd cut the clouds and morning glow
to drape over you♪

459
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:41,820
♪A single bolt of silk becomes♪

460
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:47,620
♪Your wedding gown♪
